705484f-a.title: Brooklyn: Livingston Street - Bond Street
705484f-a.text:
Livingston Street, west from Bond Street, showing more
of the north side of the street and the trolley terminal, a con-
verging point for many of Brocklyn's street car lines. Also
shown is Loeser's Department Store, extending to Elm Place: on
the west side of the latter is Namm's Department Store (white
building), and beyond that is the Abrsham and Straus store.
Views 2 and 3 show a pessenger safety isle.
View 1: November, 1935
Views 2,3: June 15, 1940
P. L. Sperr

705485f-a.title: Brooklyn: Livingston Street - Bond Street
705485f-a.text:
Livingston Street, north side, east from Bond Street to
Hanover Place. The building occupied by the Spear's furniture
people was formerly the New Montauk Theatre.
June 15, 1940
P. L. Sperr
